        <h2 id="what-is">What is review management software?</h2>
        <p>Review management software is the layer that sits between your customers and the dozen places your reviews land — Google, Facebook, Yelp, industry sites — and turns it from a chore into a system. The good ones do four things:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Request reviews automatically</strong> — SMS or email after a job, with a one-click link to leave a Google review.</li>
          <li><strong>Monitor every site</strong> — one inbox for Google, Facebook, Yelp, industry sites, plus alerts for new low-star reviews.</li>
          <li><strong>Respond at speed</strong> — AI-drafted replies you approve, or fully automated for 4-and-5-star reviews.</li>
          <li><strong>Report and rank</strong> — review velocity, star average, and the impact on Local Pack ranking.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ Watch for these red flags</div>
          <p>Avoid any tool that <strong>(a)</strong> charges per-review-collected fees on top of the monthly, <strong>(b)</strong> locks you into 12 months without a 60-day exit, or <strong>(c)</strong> asks you to "gate" 4-and-5-star reviewers separately from 1-and-2-star reviewers — that is a Google TOS violation and can get your GBP suspended.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 platforms</h2>
        <p>Same brief, same test sites, same 90-day window.</p>

